Here’s an updated version of your HTML code that includes text panels for English and Hebrew, allowing users to select text passages and indicate their alignment. The code is structured to keep everything in a single HTML file with embedded CSS and JavaScript.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Hebro Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 3fr;
            grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
            height: 100vh;
        }
        header {
            grid-column: 1 / -1;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1rem;
        }
        .sidebar {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 1rem;
            border-right: 1px solid #ccc;
        }
        .content {
            padding: 1rem;
        }
        footer {
            grid-column: 1 / -1;
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1rem;
        }
        .grid-container {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
            gap: 1rem;
        }
        .grid-item {
            background-color: #e7e7e7;
            padding: 1rem;
            text-align: center;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
        }
        .text-panel {
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 1rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            height: 150px;
            overflow-y: auto;
        }
        .align-buttons {
            margin-top: 1rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Hebro Game</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="sidebar">
        <h2>Menu</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
        <h2>Game Features</h2>
        <div class="grid-container">
            <div class="grid-item">Feature 1</div>
            <div class="grid-item">Feature 2</div>
            <div class="grid-item">Feature 3</div>
            <div class="grid-item">Feature 4</div>
            <div class="grid-item">Feature 5</div>
            <div class="grid-item">Feature 6</div>
        </div>

        <h2>Select Text</h2>
        <div class="text-panel" id="englishPanel" contenteditable="true">
            This is the English text panel. You can select and align text here.
        </div>
        <div class="text-panel" id="hebrewPanel" contenteditable="true" dir="rtl">
            זהו לוח הטקסט בעברית. אתה יכול לבחור וליישר טקסט כאן.
        </div>
        <div class="align-buttons">
            <button onclick="alignText('left')">Align Left</button>
            <button onclick="alignText('center')">Align Center</button>
            <button onclick="alignText('right')">Align Right</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 Hebro Game. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        function alignText(alignment) {
            document.execCommand('justify' + alignment);
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation of Changes:
1. **Text Panels**: Two editable text panels were added for English and Hebrew text. The Hebrew panel is set to right-to-left direction.
2. **Alignment Buttons**: Three buttons were added to allow users to align the selected text in the panels (left, center, right).
3. **JavaScript Function**: A simple JavaScript function `alignText` uses `document.execCommand` to align the selected text based on the button clicked.

This code can be saved as an HTML file and opened in a web browser to function as a web app.
